{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-product","blocks":{"product_meta":{"type":"product_meta","settings":{"show_vendor":true,"show_sku":true,"show_reviews_badge":true,"show_share_buttons":false}},"variant_selector":{"type":"variant_selector","settings":{"selector_mode":"block","color_mode":"color","show_quantity_selector":true,"show_taxes_included":false,"show_inventory_quantity":true,"low_inventory_threshold":3}},"buy_buttons":{"type":"buy_buttons","settings":{"show_payment_button":false,"show_gift_card_recipient":false}},"description":{"type":"description","disabled":true,"settings":{"display_mode":"collapse"}},"1c3d7efb-cb50-4b86-9b80-40691452b05f":{"type":"shipping_estimator","disabled":true,"settings":{"shipping_estimator_default_country":"United States","show_refunds_policy":true}}},"block_order":["product_meta","variant_selector","buy_buttons","description","1c3d7efb-cb50-4b86-9b80-40691452b05f"],"settings":{"image_size":"small","enable_video_looping":false,"enable_image_zoom":true,"zoom_effect":"outside","carousel_effect":"slide","overview_content_title_size_desktop":34,"overview_content_title_size_mobile":20,"overview_content_text_size_desktop":16,"overview_content_text_size_mobile":16}},"d6791585-88c8-43b1-8ab5-007e209ef988":{"type":"custom-html","custom_css":["p {font-size: 16px;}"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"title":"High Fidelity Images for Peace of Mind","html":"<p>The Eizo RadiForce MX217 boasts a 21.3-inch display with a 2-megapixel resolution and is calibrated to DICOM Part 14 standards, providing an optimal cost-effective monitor for viewing medical images.\n<\/p>","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"show_separator":true,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"section-top-margin-desktop":30,"section-bottom-margin-desktop":30,"section-top-margin-mobile":20,"section-bottom-margin-mobile":20,"color_title":"#eaeaea"}},"d287e6c8-9c6e-4280-82e6-95875a191b96":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"f9b6bf98-d3c1-41c4-a6a5-492025296e70":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_6.webp","image_position":"right","image_width":40,"title":"Hybrid Display of Monochrome and Color","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>The Hybrid Gamma PXL function automatically distinguishes between monochrome and color images pixel by pixel, creating a hybrid display where each pixel has optimum grayscale. As a result, monochrome images such as CT, MRI, and X-ray are displayed in the ideal grayscale that corresponds to DICOM Part 14, while color images such as 3D rendering, nuclear medicine, ultrasound, and endoscopy are faithfully reproduced corresponding to Gamma 2.2. This helps improve the efficiency of viewing both monochrome and color images by displaying them together on one sc<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["f9b6bf98-d3c1-41c4-a6a5-492025296e70"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"f244dd3a-4f37-412c-860f-c9cc34f7d212":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"2c72da9b-6782-42c0-885c-c384d721810a":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_5.webp","image_position":"left","image_width":50,"title":"Achieve Clarity True to the Source Data","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>A medical monitor needs to be capable of high brightness in order to meet performance standards. However, in order to achieve high brightness in an LCD panel, the pixel aperture ratio has to be increased. This causes a typically unavoidable decline in sharpness. With EIZO's unique Sharpness Recovery technology, the decrease in sharpness (MTF) is restored. This allows you to display an image safely on the monitor that is true to the original source data, even at high brightness levels.<br\/><br\/>MTF measures numerically how faithfully the panel transfers detail from the original image data for viewing. When Sharpness Recovery is turned on, in the case of a 2 pixel line pair (spatial frequency of 0.926 cycles\/mm) the MTF increases by over 50%.<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["2c72da9b-6782-42c0-885c-c384d721810a"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"521fc2b9-801f-49ff-beda-e8481db2f6ec":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"883a4d4b-7ccb-4a7a-a433-7df4be02a363":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/precise_diagnosis.jpg","image_position":"right","image_width":35,"title":"Make the Precise Diagnosis","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>EIZO carefully measures and sets the grayscale at the factory to ensure each monitor is compliant with DICOM Part 14. Furthermore, at startup or upon wakeup, the EIZO patented drift correction function quickly stabilizes the brightness level and compensates for the brightness fluctuations caused by the ambient temperature and the passage of time, allowing medical images to be faithfully reproduced with stable brightness and grayscale.<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":10}}},"block_order":["883a4d4b-7ccb-4a7a-a433-7df4be02a363"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"47871452-e1b1-4c3e-a9fb-d49939d74620":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"d06f201f-4f2d-49c7-915f-2425664d0c83":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_4.webp","image_position":"left","image_width":40,"title":"Elegant Cabinet Design","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>The monitor's cabinet is designed with rounded corners and elegant curves on the back to present a gentle aesthetic and facilitate a comforting environment for patients and medical staff.<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["d06f201f-4f2d-49c7-915f-2425664d0c83"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"a88ebb48-f60a-4f31-ad5e-110a98a238a7":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"f6b7cc20-73d9-40bd-914e-551fe646f4c3":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_3.webp","image_position":"right","image_width":40,"title":"Rotate the Monitor According to the Image","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>After installing the included RadiCS LE quality control software, you can link the Image Rotation Plus function with the monitor's built-in gravity sensor. This enables the screen to automatically switch to either portrait or landscape mode based on the orientation of the monitor.<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["f6b7cc20-73d9-40bd-914e-551fe646f4c3"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"a060a446-70bb-4635-b117-d1c97192d5e7":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"32ed7538-bce5-4fca-aa86-afd39665e47b":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_2.webp","image_position":"left","image_width":55,"title":"Hassle-Free Multi-Monitor Configuration","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>Using the DisplayPort connection, you can drive several monitors in a daisy chain sequence. This allows you to configure a multi-monitor setup without the complicated hassle of excessive cabling.<\/p><p><em>A graphics board that supports the daisy chain is necessary.<\/em><\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["32ed7538-bce5-4fca-aa86-afd39665e47b"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"bc73c14e-117f-4c1f-894d-b751e7ed7982":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"407f6ecb-6e79-48eb-9849-fcabaa01d84c":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_1.webp","image_position":"right","image_width":50,"title":"Manage Effortless Calibration","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>With the RadiCS LE software (included) and Integrated Front Sensor (IFS) built into the front bezel, you can easily calibrate to DICOM Part 14 without having to mount, run, and remove an external sensor.<\/p><p><em>Simple calibration using the monitor backlight sensor is also supported.<\/em><\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["407f6ecb-6e79-48eb-9849-fcabaa01d84c"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"section-top-margin-mobile":50}},"da10a63b-444e-4862-a4b2-1f3ca3fc24d3":{"type":"custom-image-with-text","blocks":{"4dc96983-4f84-4327-b9c4-19dd4c3b6e98":{"type":"Image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mx217_Product_description_compression_1.jpg","image_position":"left","image_width":45,"title":"Conserve to Preserve","title_size_desktop":23,"title_size_mobile":18,"color_heading":"#4d4d4f","content":"<p>EIZO is committed to carrying out responsible manufacturing practices to maintain high product quality while keeping the environment in mind. The MX217 is made of approximately 18% recycled plastic. This mitigates the amount of plastic waste going into the environment, conserves resources, and promotes the reuse of materials for preserving natural ecosystems.<\/p>","text_size_desktop":15,"text_size_mobile":14,"color_text":"#4d4d4f","button_text":"","button_link":"","show_separator":true,"color_title":"#eaeaea","image_gap":0}}},"block_order":["4dc96983-4f84-4327-b9c4-19dd4c3b6e98"],"settings":{"show_section_margin":false,"top-margin-desktop":30,"bottom-margin-desktop":30,"top-margin-mobile":20,"bottom-margin-mobile":20,"show_section_top_margin":false,"section-top-margin-desktop":80,"sec